# Cursor IDE — ModMe / next-forge

Adapted from [araguaci/cursor-skills](https://github.com/araguaci/cursor-skills) (MIT) and ModMe monorepo boundaries.

## Environment setup (mandatory)

1. Root `.env` → run `.\scripts\sync-env-from-root.ps1` before next-forge dev
2. Package manager: **Bun** in `next-forge/` only (`yarn dev:forge:*` from root)
3. Ports: app **3100**, web **3101**, api **3102**, docs **3104**, storybook **6106**
## gh-aw secrets (ADR-0010)

- Root `.env` (gitignored) is the single local source of truth
- `yarn setup:env` → next-forge dotenv; `yarn setup:gh-aw` → GitHub `COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN`
- Workflows default `engine: copilot`; extension v0.79.8+
- Windows: compile in WSL or CI only

## Project structure

- `next-forge/apps/` — deployable apps
- `next-forge/packages/` — `@repo/*` shared code
- Never `workspace:*` or relative imports across `next-forge/` ↔ `GenerativeUI_monorepo/`
- Feature work in Git worktrees, not main checkout

## Code quality (cursor-skills aligned)

- TypeScript strict; Zod validation at component boundaries
- Functional React components; Server Components first
- Early returns for errors; no deep nesting
- kebab-case files/dirs; PascalCase components; camelCase hooks/props

## gh-aw workflow rules

- Edit `.github/workflows/*.md` only — never hand-edit `.lock.yml`
- After frontmatter changes: `gh aw compile`
- Trigger runs: `gh aw run <name>` (not `gh workflow run *.lock.yml`)
- Writes via `safe-outputs` only; agent jobs stay read-only

## DX commands

```powershell
.\scripts\setup-modme-dev.ps1    # full env + gh-aw + forge verify
yarn dev:forge:core              # core stack
yarn verify:forge                # CI parity
gh aw compile --validate         # agentic workflows
```

## Review checklist

- [ ] Env synced; no secrets committed
- [ ] Correct monorepo boundary respected
- [ ] gh-aw lock files regenerated if `.md` changed
- [ ] `yarn check:forge` passes for next-forge edits
